    <body>
      <section eId="sec_453">
        <num>453</num>
        <heading>Treasurers of hospitals; appointment</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_453__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The commissioner may appoint such an officer for each hospital.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_453__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>In the event that the commissioner fails to appoint a treasurer as\nprovided by this section, or in the event of a vacancy occurring in the\noffice of treasurer or pending the appointment of a treasurer, the\ndirector of the hospital shall be the treasurer.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_453__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>During the absence or disability of the treasurer of a hospital,\nthe director thereof shall perform the duties of a treasurer.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
